title: Air Fryer Roasted Asparagus
description: Tender, crisp, air fryer asparagus with Parmesan cheese that's ready in minutes. This delicious roast vegetable recipe is perfect for busy weeknights.
directions: Step1: Preheat the air fryer to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C). Line the basket with parchment paper. Step2: Place asparagus spears in the prepared basket and mist with avocado oil. Sprinkle with garlic powder, salt, pepper, and pepper flakes. Top with Parmesan cheese. Step3: Air-fry until asparagus spears start to char, 7 to 9 minutes.
ingredients: 1 bunch fresh asparagus, trimmed, avocado oil cooking spray, 0.5 teaspoon garlic powder, 0.5 teaspoon Himalayan pink salt, 0.25 teaspoon ground multi-colored peppercorns, 0.25 teaspoon red pepper flakes, 0.25 cup freshly grated Parmesan cheese

title: Crab Rangoon in the Air Fryer
description: Crab rangoon turn extra crispy when cooked in the air fryer. Filled with crab, cream cheese, and spices these little crab puffs are a tasty Chinese-American treat.
directions: Step1: Stir together apricot spread, chili-garlic sauce, soy sauce, orange zest, and orange juice in a small bowl for the dipping sauce. Step2: Preheat air fryer to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Step3: Stir together cream cheese, crab, chives, Worcestershire, garlic, pepper, and salt in a bowl for the filling. Arrange 6 wonton wrappers on a work surface. Keep remaining wrappers covered until ready to use to prevent them from drying out. Step4: Spoon about 2 teaspoon crab filling in center of each wrapper. Lightly wet borders of wrapper with water. Bring together the 2 opposite corners of the wrapper over the filling and seal together. Bring remaining 2 corners up toward the center, sealing edges of the wrapper to enclose the filling. Repeat with remaining wrappers and filling. Step5: Working in batches if needed, coat dumplings with cooking spray and arrange in an even layer in the air fryer basket. Step6: Cook until dumplings are crispy and golden brown, about 8 minutes. Serve with sauce.
ingredients: 1/2 cup seedless apricot fruit spread, 1 tablespoon chili-garlic sauce, 1 tablespoon less-sodium soy sauce, 1/2 teaspoon orange zest                                                          , 2 tablespoons fresh juice (from 1 orange), 4 un cream cheese, 4 ounces fresh lump crabmeat, drained, 2 tablespoons chopped fresh chives, 2 teaspoon Worcestershire sauce, 1 clove garlic, grated (1/2 teaspoon), 1/4 teaspoon freshly ground black pepper, 1/8 teaspoon salt, 18 wonton wrappers

title: Air Fryer Scrambled Eggs On The Go
description: A quick and easy way to make scrambled eggs in your air fryer to take on the go if you're in a hurry.
directions: Step1: Lightly spray a ramekin dish with non-stick cooking spray. Pour in beaten eggs. Step2: Set air fryer to 370 degrees F (185 degrees C) and place the ramekin into the air fryer basket. Step3: Air fry for 3 minutes. Stir egg mixture and cook for 3 minutes more. Fluff with a fork and season to taste with salt and pepper. Grab and go.
ingredients: cooking spray, 2 large eggs, beaten, salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste

title: Air Fryer Sweet Potato Fries
description: These crispy air fryer sweet potato fries, seasoned with garlic and paprika, are simply addictive and take only 10 minutes to cook.
directions: Step1: Preheat the air fryer to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C). Step2: Cut sweet potato into 1/2-inch wide fries. Place in a bowl with canola oil; toss to coat. Season with salt, pepper, garlic powder, and paprika; mix until all fries are evenly coated. Step3: Working in batches if necessary, place an even layer of fries in the air fryer basket. Step4: Cook in the preheated air fryer until golden, about 10 minutes. Repeat to cook remaining fries. Step5: Serve hot and enjoy!
ingredients: 1 medium sweet potato, peeled, 1 tablespoon canola oil, 0.5 teaspoon kosher salt, 0.25 teaspoon pepper, 0.125 teaspoon garlic powder, 0.125 teaspoon ground sweet paprika

title: Air Fryer Everything-Bagel Salmon Dinner
description: Salmon fillets are flavored with everything bagel seasoning and cooked in the air fyer with sweet potatoes and broccoli. A perfectly balanced meal for 2 on a weekday.
directions: Step1: Preheat air fryer to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C). Coat a sheet of foil with cooking spray. Step2: Toss sweet potatoes with 1 1/2 teaspoons oil and 1/8 teaspoon each salt and pepper in a bowl. Arrange sweet potatoes in an even layer on the foil; transfer to the air fryer basket. Cook until mostly tender, about 10 minutes. Step3: Meanwhile, stir together mustard, honey, and mayonnaise in a small bowl. In another bowl, toss broccoli with remaining 1 1/2 teaspoons oil and 1/8 teaspoon each salt and pepper. Step4: Push sweet potatoes to one side of the basket. Add salmon to the other side. Spoon 1 teaspoon mustard mixture onto each fillet; spread to coat tops of fillets. Sprinkle evenly with bagel seasoning. Arrange broccoli around sweet potatoes and salmon. Cook until salmon is opaque and flakes easily with a fork and sweet potatoes and broccoli are tender, 10 to 14 minutes. Step5: Stir soy sauce into the remaining mustard mixture; drizzle over sweet potatoes and broccoli to serve.
ingredients: 1 sweet potato (8 ounces), cut into 1/4-inch wedges [You should get about 11/2 cups wedges.], 3 teaspoon olive oil, 1/4 teaspoon salt, 1/4 teaspoon freshly ground black pepper, 1 tablespoon Dijon mustard, 1 tablespoon honey, 2 teaspoon mayonnaise, 2 cups small broccoli florets, 2 (5- to 6-ounces) salmon fillets, about 1 inch thick, 2 teaspoon everything bagel seasoning, 1 teaspoon less-sodium soy sauce

title: Air Fryer Loaded Mashed Potato Cakes
description: Turn your leftover mashed potatoes into these cheesy mashed potato cakes cooked in the air fryer.
directions: Step1: Combine mashed potatoes, Cheddar cheese, green onions, bacon bits, and flour in a bowl; stir until combined. Mix in beaten egg. Step2: Preheat air fryer to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C) for 10 minutes. Step3: Form mixture into 6 patties and set on a baking sheet. Place baking sheet in the freezer for 10 minutes while you preheat the air fryer. Step4: Place patties in the air fryer basket in batches, making sure to not overcrowd. Cook undisturbed for 12 minutes. Repeat with remaining patties.
ingredients: 2 cups cold mashed potatoes, 1 cup shredded Cheddar cheese, 3 green onions, chopped, 0.25 cup real bacon bits, 2 tablespoons all-purpose flour, 1 small egg, beaten

title: Air Fryer Tempura Vegetables
description: The air fryer makes it easy to cook tempura vegetables. With this formula you can create your own customized tempura-battered veggies by using different vegetables, seasonings, and dipping sauces.
directions: Step1: Preheat air fryer to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Step2: Beat egg whites in a bowl until frothy. Whisk in seltzer water until combined. Whisk in flour, SEASONING, salt, and pepper until batter forms. Step3: Coat basket with cooking spray. Dip VEGETABLES into batter until coated; allow excess to drip off. Working in batches if needed, arrange vegetables in an even layer in basket. Cook until golden brown, about 7 minutes. Serve with DIPPING SAUCE.
ingredients: 2 egg whites, 1/4 cup plain seltzer water, 1/2 cup flour, 1/4 teaspoon seasoning, 1/2 teaspoon salt, 1/4 teaspoon freshly ground black pepper, 2 cups vegetables, Purchased DIPPING SAUCE, for serving

title: Basic Air Fryer Hot Dogs
description: Air fryer hot dogs with perfectly toasted buns are ready to serve with your favorite condiments in just five minutes and require minimal cleanup!
directions: Step1: Preheat an air fryer to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C). Step2: Place buns in a single layer in the air fryer basket; cook in the preheated air fryer until crisp, about 2 minutes. Remove buns to a plate. Step3: Place hot dogs in a single layer in the air fryer basket; cook for 3 minutes. Serve hot dogs in toasted buns.
ingredients: 4 hot dog buns, 4 hot dogs

title: Air Fryer Mini Croissants with Nutella and Jam
description: These mini croissants filled with Nutella and jam are made with puff pastry and cooked in the air fryer.
directions: Step1: Preheat air fryer to 300 degrees F (150 degrees C). Step2: Roll out puff pastry on a lightly floured surface into a large square, about 12 inches. Cut into 4 equal squares, and then cut each square in half diagonally, making 8 triangles. Step3: Position the triangle so the wide end is facing you, and the point is away from you. Dip your finger tip in some water, and moisten the edges of each triangle. Whisk the egg and tablespoon of water in a small bowl, and set aside. Step4: Add about 1 teaspoon Nutella to the center, and top with about 1/2 teaspoon strawberry jam. Starting on the wide end, roll up dough over the filling toward the point, pinching in the dough, so the filling doesn't ooze out, and shaping the ends into a crescent shape. Brush each crescent with egg wash and sprinkle with cinnamon sugar. Step5: Line your air fryer basket with a parchment liner or spray with cooking spray. Place the croissants into your air fryer basket, seam side down, so they're not touching. Step6: Cook in the air fryer until golden brown,11 to 14 minutes. Your cooking time may vary depending on the size and brand of your air fryer. Step7: Transfer to a wire rack and cool for 5 minutes. Serve warm.
ingredients: 1 sheet frozen puff pastry, thawed, 1 large egg, 1 tablespoon water, 8 teaspoons chocolate-hazelnut spread (such as Nutella®), 4 teaspoons strawberry jam, 1 teaspoon cinnamon sugar, or as needed

title: Air Fryer Bacon Wrapped Brussels Sprouts
description: Air fryer bacon wrapped Brussels sprouts are a quick and easy side dish.
directions: Step1: Preheat the air fryer to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C). Step2: Place halved Brussels sprouts in a bowl; sprinkle with steak seasoning and toss to coat. Step3: Wrap a half slice of bacon around a Brussels sprout half and place seam-side-down in the basket of the air fryer. Repeat with remaining bacon and Brussels sprouts. Step4: Cook for 10 minutes undisturbed. Using tongs, transfer to a plate and serve immediately.
ingredients: 1 pound Brussels sprouts, trimmed and halved (12 sprouts), 2 teaspoons Montreal steak seasoning, 12 slices bacon, halved widthwise

title: Air Fryer Chicken Thighs
description: These air fryer chicken thighs are incredibly juicy with crisp skin. Ready in 30 minutes, these tasty paprika-rubbed chicken thighs are always a hit!
directions: Step1: Preheat an air fryer to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C). Step2: Pat chicken thighs dry with a paper towel and brush skins with olive oil. Place chicken thighs, skin-side down, in a single layer on a plate. Step3: Combine smoked paprika, garlic powder, salt, and pepper in a bowl. Sprinkle 1/2 of the seasoning mixture evenly over thighs. Turn thighs over and evenly sprinkle with remaining seasoning. Arrange thighs, skin-side up, in a single layer in the air fryer basket. Step4: Cook in the preheated air fryer until thighs are brown and the juices run clear, about 18 minutes. An instant-read thermometer inserted into the center should read at least 165 degrees F (74 degrees C).
ingredients: 4 skin-on, boneless chicken thighs, 2 teaspoons extra-virgin olive oil, 1 teaspoon smoked paprika, 0.75 teaspoon garlic powder, 0.5 teaspoon salt, 0.5 teaspoon ground black pepper

title: Air Fryer Potato Wedges
description: Deliciously crispy air-fried potato wedges that are perfectly seasoned and ready to serve in just over 30 minutes. It doesn't get any easier than this!
directions: Step1: Preheat an air fryer to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C). Step2: Cut each potato in half lengthwise. Cut each half in half lengthwise, and then cut each quarter in half lengthwise. You will have 16 wedges. Gather the seasonings. Step3: Place potato wedges in a large bowl. Add olive oil, paprika, parsley, chili, salt, and pepper; mix until well combined. Step4: Place 1/2 of the potato wedges in the basket of the air fryer and cook for 10 minutes. Step5: Flip wedges with tongs and cook for an additional 5 minutes. Remove to a plate. Step6: Repeat to cook the remaining wedges. Step7: Serve hot and enjoy!
ingredients: 2 medium russet potatoes, 1.5 tablespoons olive oil, 0.5 teaspoon ground paprika, 0.5 teaspoon parsley flakes, 0.5 teaspoon chili powder, 0.5 teaspoon sea salt, 0.125 teaspoon ground black pepper

title: Air Fryer Meatloaf
description: This flavorful air fryer meatloaf recipe is incredibly easy to make, requires simple ingredients, and is ready to eat in just under an hour.
directions: Step1: Preheat an air fryer to 392 degrees F (200 degrees C). Step2: Combine ground beef, onion, bread crumbs, thyme, egg, salt, and pepper in a bowl. Knead and mix thoroughly. Transfer mixture to a small loaf pan. Smooth the top, press in mushrooms, and coat with olive oil. Step3: Roast meatloaf in the preheated air fryer until nicely browned, about 25 minutes. An instant-read thermometer inserted into the center should read at least 165 degrees F (72 degrees C). Step4: Let meatloaf rest at least 10 minutes before slicing into wedges and serving.
ingredients: 1 pound lean ground beef, 1 small onion, finely chopped, 1 large egg, lightly beaten, 3 tablespoons dry bread crumbs, 1 tablespoon chopped fresh thyme, 1 teaspoon salt, ground black pepper to taste, 2 mushrooms, thickly sliced, 1 tablespoon olive oil, or as needed

title: Air Fryer Sweet Potato Chips
description: Use your air fryer to make these yummy sweet potato chips. The best chips came from a mandoline that was set just a hair thicker than 1/16 inch (about 3/32 inch thick) after much experimenting.
directions: Step1: Slice potato into 1/16-inch-thick rounds using a mandoline. Put potato slices in a large bowl of cold water; soak about 20 minutes. Drain and pat dry with paper towels. Wipe out bowl. Step2: Return potato slices to dried bowl. Add oil, salt, and pepper; toss gently to coat. Step3: Preheat air fryer to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Lightly coat air fryer basket with cooking spray. Working in batches if needed, arrange potato slices in an even layer in basket (do not overcrowd). Step4: Cook until lightly golden and crispy, 12 to 16 minutes, turning and rearranging chips into an even layer every 4 minutes. Watch closely during the last 2 to 3 minutes of cooking. Check chips about every 30 seconds, using tongs to remove golden chips from the basket as needed to avoid overcooking and ending up with bitter chips. Step5: Let chips cool about 5 minutes. Chips will continue to crisp as they cool.Store in an airtight container up to 3 days.
ingredients: 1 (8-ounces) sweet potato, 1 tablespoon canola oil, 1/4 teaspoon sea salt, 1/4 teaspoon freshly ground black pepper

title: Air Fryer Pecan Crusted Trout
description: This pecan crusted trout cooked in the air fryer is a quick and easy dinner that is on the table in 20 minutes. Serve with vegetables and rice.
directions: Step1: Preheat air fryer to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C). Step2: Stir together pecans, rosemary, and salt in a shallow dish. In a second shallow dish, add flour. In a third shallow dish, lightly beat egg. Dip one side of each fillet in flour, shaking off excess; dip into egg, then into pecan mixture, lightly pressing to coat fish. Step3: Working in batches if needed, arrange fillets on parchment paper, pecan-coating up. Transfer fish on parchment to the air fryer basket. Step4: Cook until fish easily flakes with a fork and an instant-read thermometer inserted into thickest part of fillets registers 145 degrees F (62 degrees C), 7 to 8 minutes. Step5:  Drizzle fillets with maple syrup and serve with lemon wedges.
ingredients: 2/3 cup finely chopped pecans, 1 teaspoon dried rosemary, crushed, 1/2 teaspoon salt, 2 tablespoons flour, 1 egg, 4 (4-ounces) rainbow trout fillets, thawed iffrozen, skinned if desired, 2 teaspoon pure maple syrup, Lemon wedges, for serving

title: Air Fryer Turtle Cheesecake
description: Did you know that you can use your air fryer to make turtle cheesecake? The flavors of chocolate, caramel, toasted pecans, and creamy cheesecake are a perfect match.
directions: Step1: Line the bottom of a 7- to 7 1/2-inch springform pan or cake pan with parchment paper. Stir together graham crackers and 1 tablespoon sugar in a bowl. Stir in melted butter. Press crumb mixture into the bottom and 1 inch up the sides of the prepared pan. Step2: For the filling, combine cream cheese, sour cream, 1/3 cup sugar, lemon juice, vanilla, and salt in a bowl. Beat with an electric mixer at medium-high speed until smooth. Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating at low speed just until combined. Pour filling over the crust. Arrange pan in the air fryer basket. Step3: Set air fryer to 300 degrees F (150 degrees C). Step4: Cook for 15 minutes. Reduce temperature to 240 degrees F (115 degrees C) and cook 20 minutes more. The center of the cheesecake will appear wet and may jiggle slightly. Transfer cheesecake to a wire rack. Let stand about 15 minutes. Using a small sharp knife or thin spatula, loosen cheesecake from sides of pan; let stand until completely cooled, about 30 minutes more. Remove cheesecake from pan. Chill, covered, at least 4 hours or up to overnight. Step5: To serve, drizzle with chocolate and caramel ice cream toppings and sprinkle with pecans.
ingredients: 1 cup graham cracker crumbs, 1/3 cup plus 1 tablespoon sugar, 6 tablespoon butter, melted, 12 ounces cream cheese, softened, 1/3 cup sour cream, 1 teaspoon lemon juice, 1 teaspoon vanilla extract, 1 pinch salt, 2 eggs, chocolate ice cream topping, caramel ice cream topping, chopped toasted pecans

title: Air Fryer Pretzel Crescent Rolls
description: A quick and easy recipe for crispy pretzel crescent rolls cooked in the air fryer.
directions: Step1: Place a large stock pot over high heat. Add water and bring to a boil over high heat. Step2: Meanwhile shape crescents into desired shape and preheat air fryer to 350° Step3: Preheat an air fryer to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Line the air fryer basket with a fitted piece of parchment. Generously spray with cooking spray. Step4: Once water is boiling, carefully add baking soda (it WILL bubble up!). Lower crescent rolls into the brine with a spider strainer; boil for 5 seconds. Transfer onto the parchment paper in the air fryer basket. Sprinkle with salt. Step5: Air fry until crescent rolls are cooked through and golden, about 12 minutes. Serve immediately.
ingredients: 1 quart water, 0.25 cup baking soda, 1 (8 ounce) package refrigerated crescent roll dough, pretzel salt, cooking spray

title: Air Fryer Loaded Egg Salad Sandwiches
description: Instead of hard-boiling eggs, air-fry them. Serve this salad in your favorite sandwich bread.
directions: Step1: Preheat air fryer to 250 degrees F (120 degrees C). Step2: Arrange whole eggs in shells in an even layer in the fryer basket; cook for 20 minutes. Immediately plunge eggs into an ice bath. Let stand until cool, about 5 minutes; drain. Peel and coarsely chop eggs Step3: Meanwhile, stir together bacon, celery, mayonnaise, onion, relish, mustard, sriracha, dill, Worcestershire, black pepper, paprika, and salt in a large bowl. Gently stir chopped eggs into mayonnaise mixture until combined. Chill, covered, at least 1 hour or up to 3 days. Serve egg salad in bread with lettuce.
ingredients: 8 eggs, 4 slices bacon, crisp-cooked and crumbled, 2 stalks celery, finely chopped (3/4 cup), 1/4 cup mayonnaise, 2 tablespoons thinly sliced green onion, 2 teaspoon sweet pickle relish, 2 teaspoon yellow mustard, 2 teaspoon sriracha sauce, 3/4 teaspoon dried dill, 1/2 teaspoon Worcestershire sauce, 1/2 teaspoon freshly ground black pepper, 1/4 teaspoon paprika, 1/8 teaspoon salt, 8 slices whole-grain seeded bread, 4 leaves romaine lettuce, torn

title: Easy Air Fryer Pork Chops
description: These air fryer pork chops have a crispy Parmesan crust, but are super tender and juicy inside — a great option for a quick and delicious dinner.
directions: Step1: Preheat the air fryer to 380 degrees F (190 degrees C). Step2: Combine Parmesan cheese, paprika, garlic powder, salt, parsley, and pepper in a flat shallow dish; mix well. Step3: Coat each pork chop with olive oil. Dredge both sides of each chop in the Parmesan mixture and set on a plate. Step4: Place 2 chops in the basket of the air fryer and cook for 10 minutes; flipping halfway through cook time. Transfer to a cutting board and let rest for 5 minutes. Repeat with remaining chops. Step5: Served hot and enjoy!
ingredients: 0.5 cup grated Parmesan cheese, 1 teaspoon paprika, 1 teaspoon garlic powder, 1 teaspoon kosher salt, 1 teaspoon dried parsley, 0.5 teaspoon ground black pepper, 4 (5 ounce) boneless pork chops, 2 tablespoons extra virgin olive oil

title: Air Fryer Pizza
description: Use your air fryer to make personal pizzas which can be easily be customized to everyone's liking.
directions: Step1: Preheat the air fryer for 5 minutes at 380 degrees F (190 degrees C). Spray the air fryer basket with olive oil spray or line with a parchment liner to avoid sticking. Step2: Remove crust from the can, and cut in half. Shape each piece of dough into a circle and crimping up the edges to form a crust. Make sure it'll fit in your air fryer basket. Carefully transfer one pizza crust to the air fryer basket and spray lightly with olive oil spray. Prick the dough with a fork and precook for 3 minutes. Step3: Spread 3 tablespoons pizza sauce onto the crust in the air fryer basket and sprinkle with 1/2 of the mozzarella cheese. Top with 7 pepperoni slices and half of the onion slices. Sprinkle with basil and red pepper flakes, if using. Step4: Cook until crust is golden brown and crispy and the cheese has melted, 7 to 9 minutes. Keep in mind that cooking times may vary depending on the brand and size of your air fryer, so check frequently to be sure nothing overcooks or burns. Repeat procedure with the second pizza crust. Serve hot.
ingredients: olive oil cooking spray, 1 (13.8 ounce) package refrigerated pizza dough (such as Pillsbury®), 6 tablespoons pizza sauce, divided, 10 ounces shredded mozzarella cheese, divided, 14 slices pepperoni, divided, 0.5 cup onion slices, divided, sprinkle of dried basil and red pepper flakes (optional)

title: Air Fryer Meatballs
description: Air fryer meatballs are quick, easy, and mess-free to make. The insides stay tender and juicy while the outsides brown up nicely. Serve with marinara.
directions: Step1: Preheat an air fryer to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Step2: Combine beef, pork, Parmesan cheese, bread crumbs, egg, garlic, Italian seasoning, and salt in a large bowl. Mix until evenly combined. Form into 16 equal meatballs (a small ice cream scoop is helpful) and place on a baking sheet. Step3: Place 1/2 of the meatballs in the basket of the air fryer and cook 8 minutes. Shake the basket and cook 2 minutes more. Transfer to a serving plate and let rest for 5 minutes. Repeat with remaining meatballs.
ingredients: 16 ounces lean ground beef, 4 ounces ground pork, 0.5 cup grated Parmesan cheese, 0.33333334326744 cup Italian seasoned bread crumbs, 1 egg, 2 cloves garlic, minced, 1 teaspoon Italian seasoning, 0.5 teaspoon salt

title: Air Fryer Halloumi Cheese
description: A simple 2-ingredient recipe for a delicious halloumi cheese appetizer made in the air fryer.
directions: Step1: Preheat the air fryer to 360 degrees F (180 degrees C). Step2: Slice halloumi into 6 equal slices, cut each slice in half, and dry with a paper towel. Brush all sides with olive oil. Step3: Lightly spray the air fryer basket with cooking spray. Place the halloumi slices in the basket, making sure they're not touching. You may have to cook in two batches, Step4: Cook for 7 to 9 minutes until golden brown, but make sure not to overcook or they turn rubbery. Serve immediately.
ingredients: 8 ounces halloumi cheese, 2 teaspoons olive oil, cooking spray

title: Air Fryer Spanakopita
description: The classic Greek appetizer spanakopita can easily be made in the air fryer.
directions: Step1: For filling, stir together spinach, feta, mozzarella, Parmesan, and garlic in a bowl. Line a baking sheet with parchment paper. Step2: Arrange 1 sheet of phyllo on a clean work surface and brush lightly with some of the melted butter. Top with 2 more phyllo sheets and more butter. Cover remaining phyllo with a damp towel while you work. Cut phyllo stack lengthwise into 3 (3-inch-wide) strips. Step3: Spoon about 1 tablespoon filling at the bottom of each strip. Take the bottom right corner and fold the dough over the filling to make a triangle. Fold the bottom left corner up to make another triangle. Continue folding until all the dough is folded. Arrange spanakopita, seam side down, on the prepared baking sheet. Lightly brush with butter. Repeat with remaining phyllo, filling, and butter. Step4: Preheat air fryer to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C) Step5: Arrange spanakopita in an even layer in the air fryer basket, working in batches as needed. Step6: Cook, turning once halfway through, until spanakopita is golden brown, 12 to 15 minutes. Cool slightly. Serve with tzatziki sauce and dill.
ingredients: 2 (10-ounces) pkg. frozen chopped spinach, thawed and squeezed dry, 1/2 cup crumbled feta cheese, 1/2 cup shredded mozzarella cheese, 1/2 cup grated Parmesan cheese, 1 clove garlic, minced, 1 (1-lb.) pkg. frozen phyllo dough, thawed, 1/2 cup unsalted butter, melted, tzatziki sauce for serving, chopped fresh dill forserving

title: Quick Air Fryer Tilapia
description: This lightly breaded tilapia fillet cooks in 7 minutes in the air fryer.
directions: Step1: Preheat an air fryer to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C). Spray the air fryer basket with olive oil spray or line with a parchment liner. Step2: Whisk flour, seafood seasoning, paprika, garlic powder, salt, and pepper together in a small bowl. Step3: Remove tilapia filets from the package and pat dry with a paper towel. Lightly spray filets with olive oil, and sprinkle flour seasoning over each filet, pressing down to coat all of the fish. Turn them over, and season on the other side as well. Place the filets into the air fryer basket, without overlapping, so air can circulate around the filets. Step4: Cook until tilapia filets flake easily with a fork, 7 to 10 minutes. There is no need to flip them. Depending on your air fryer size, you might have to cook them in batches. Step5: Top each filet with a slice of lemon, and serve hot.
ingredients: olive oil cooking spray, 2 tablespoons all-purpose flour, 1.5 teaspoons seafood seasoning (such as Old Bay®), 0.75 teaspoon paprika, 0.5 teaspoon garlic powder, salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste, 1 pound tilapia fillets, thawed if frozen, 4 lemon slices

title: Air Fryer Crispy Pickle Chips with Creole Dipping Sauce
description: Crispy pickle chips easily cooked in the air fryer. Serve with homemade Creole dipping sauce for a tasty snack.
directions: Step1: Preheat air fryer to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Lightly coat air fryer basket with cooking spray. Step2: Put flour in a shallow dish. In a second shallow dish, lightly beat eggs. In a third shallow dish, add panko. Pat pickle chips very dry. Coat pickles in flour, shaking off excess. Dip in eggs, allowing excess to drip off. Toss in panko, lightly pressing to adhere. Arrange pickles in the air fryer basket in an even layer (do not overcrowd), working in batches if needed. Step3: Cook until pickle chips are golden brown, about 6 minutes. Step4: Meanwhile, stir together mayonnaise, Creole mustard, lemon juice, and smoked paprika in a small bowl. Serve dipping sauce with pickles.
ingredients: 1/2 cup flour, 2 eggs, 1 cup panko bread crumbs, 1 (16-ounces) jar reduced-sodium dill picklechips, drained, 1/4 cup mayonnaise, 1 tablespoon Creole mustard

title: Spicy Chicken Jerky in the Air Fryer
description: This spicy chicken jerky recipe is made in the air fryer and flavored with mojo criollo marinade and Cajun seasoning.
directions: Step1: Combine chicken strips, marinade, and Cajun seasoning in a resealable plastic bag. Refrigerate for 8 hours to overnight. Step2: Measure skewers to fit across the air fryer basket, slightly overlapping the edge. Trim off excess length. Step3: Preheat the air fryer to 180 degrees F (80 degrees C) for 10 minutes. Step4: Thread chicken strips onto skewers, leaving room in between each strip, while the air fryer is preheating. Step5: Air fry for 1 hour 15 minutes. Adjust cooking time as most air fryers have a maximum setting of 30 minutes. Rearrange the skewers during the reset time. Step6: Increase temperature to 200 degrees F (95 degrees C) and air fry for an additional 15 minutes. Step7: Remove strips to a paper towel-lined storage container. Seal. Allow to rest overnight before serving.
ingredients: 2 (5 ounce) boneless chicken breasts, cut into strips, 0.5 cup mojo criollo marinade (such as Goya®), 2 teaspoons Cajun seasoning, 6 wooden skewers

title: Air Fryer Grilled Ham and Cheese
description: A grilled ham and cheese sandwich is the ultimate comfort food, and now it’s easier than ever using the air fryer.
directions: Step1: Spread mayonnaise on one side of each slice of bread. With mayo side down, lightly spread 4 slices of bread with Dijon mustard, evenly top each with Swiss cheese, ham slices, folded to fit, and pickle slices. Place the remaining 4 bread slices on the sandwiches, mayo side up, and lightly press sandwiches to close. Step2: Preheat the air fryer to 380 degrees F (193 degrees C). Spray the air fryer basket with cooking spray or line with a parchment liner. Step3: Place sandwiches in the air fryer basket in a single layer, leaving some space around them. You may have to cook the sandwiches in batches, depending on the size of your fryer. Step4: Cook until sandwiches begin to brown, 3 to 4 minutes. Flip, and cook until cheese has melted and sandwiches are golden brown, 2 to 3 minutes more. Slice sandwiches in half and serve warm.
ingredients: 2 tablespoons mayonnaise, 8 slices white bread, 2 tablespoons Dijon mustard, or to taste, 8 slices deli ham, 4 large slices Swiss cheese, 8 dill pickle slices, Cooking spray

title: Air Fryer Cheese Curds
description: These air fryer cheese curds give you the nice golden color of traditionally fried cheese curds, but allow the ooey gooey cheese to be the star.
directions: Step1: For Aioli: Combine garlic cloves, olive oil, and the 1/2 teaspoon soul seasoning in a small bowl and toss to coat. Wrap garlic tightly in a small piece of foil. Step2: Preheat the air fryer to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C). Place wrapped garlic in the air fryer basket, and air fry for 15 minutes. Step3: Remove garlic from the air fryer and place in a small bowl. Mash roasted garlic with the back of a spoon. Let stand for 30 minutes. Step4: Stir mayonnaise and lemon juice into the mashed garlic until well combined. Cover and refrigerate for 30 minutes before serving. Step5: For Cheese Curds: Place cheese curds on a large rimmed baking sheet lined with parchment paper. Place the tray with cheese curds in the freezer for 30 minutes. Step6: Meanwhile, whisk flour and 1 teaspoon soul seasoning together in a shallow bowl. Whisk eggs and milk together In a separate bowl until smooth and cohesive. Stir panko and remaining 3 teaspoons soul seasoning together in a third shallow bowl.  Step7: Remove cheese curds from the freezer. Working in batches, dip cheese curds into the flour to coat well, then into the egg mixture, making sure to shake off any excess. Dip curds again in flour mixture and again into egg mixture. Finally, dip curds into panko to fully coat with breadcrumbs. Use your dry hand to pack on panko so that it sticks well. Place breaded cheese curds back onto the baking sheet. When all cheese curds are breaded, return the baking sheet to the freezer for 30 minutes. Step8: Preheat the air fryer to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Remove tray from freezer. Using a mister, lightly spray both sides of the cheese curds with vegetable oil. Coat the air fryer basket with nonstick cooking spray. Step9: Working in batches, place cheese curds in the air fryer basket in a single layer. Air fry until golden brown and crispy on both sides, flipping halfway through cooking time, 4 to 6 minutes. Step10: Let stand in the air fryer for 1 to 2 minutes before serving. Serve with roasted garlic aioli.
ingredients: 10 Ounces Cheese curds, 1-1/4 Cups All-purpose flour*, 4 Teaspoons  soul food seasoning (such as JBJ Soul Kitchen Soul Seasoning), divided, 1 Large Egg, 1-1/2 Cups Milk, 2-1/4 Cups Panko bread crumbs**, Oil for spraying, Nonstick cooking spray

title: Air Fryer Caramelized Bananas
description: This is one of the easiest, no-fuss sweet treats you’ll ever make. There are many ways to serve caramelized bananas, but our favorite way is over vanilla ice cream or vanilla Greek yogurt.
directions: Step1: Preheat air fryer to 390 degrees F (195 degrees C) Step2: Spread out banana slices on a plate. Combine butter and vanilla extract and drizzle over the bananas. Step3: Combine brown sugar and cinnamon. Sprinkle half of the sugar mixture over the slices, flip, and sprinkle the remaining sugar over the other side. Make sure both sides are well coated. Step4: Spray the air fryer basket with cooking spray or line with a parchment paper. Step5: Place banana slices in the air fryer basket in a single layer making sure not to overcrowd or overlap. Cook until golden brown and caramelized to your liking, 7 to 9 minutes. You do not need to flip banana slices over. Step6: Remove bananas from the basket, cool slightly, and serve.
ingredients: 2 large firm bananas, 1 tablespoon melted salted butter, 1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract, 1 tablespoon brown sugar, 1/2 teaspoon ground cinnamon

title: Air Fryer Waffle Egg in a Hole
description: This fun twist on a classic egg-in-a-hole is made in the air fryer for easy cooking and clean-up. Plus, the toaster waffle adds a delicious buttery flavor and crisp texture.
directions: Step1: Preheat the air fryer to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Step2: Cut a hole in the center of the frozen waffle using the rim of a cup or glass (about 2 to 3 inches in diameter). Move waffle to a square of parchment paper, then carefully place the parchment paper into the preheated air fryer, along with the small center waffle.  Step3: Crack egg directly into the center of waffle hole; season with salt and pepper to taste. Close the lid and cook until the white of the egg has started to set, about 5 to 6 minutes. Step4: Remove small center waffle from the air fryer. Sprinkle shredded cheese onto egg waffle, and cook until the cheese is melted and egg white is completely set, about 1 to 2 minutes. Step5: Transfer egg waffle onto a plate; drizzle with maple syrup and serve immediately.
ingredients: 1 large egg

title: Air Fryer Roasted Vegetables with Gremolata and Red Pepper Aioli
description: Air fryer roasted vegetables come out wonderfully crisp and tender—paired with homemade gremolada and red pepper aioli they make a tasty appetizer or side.
directions: Step1: Preheat air fryer to 360 degrees F (180 degrees C). Step2: Combine zucchini, summer squash, mushrooms, cauliflower, bell peppers, oil, salt, and black pepper in a bowl; toss to coat. Arrange vegetables in an even layer in the air fryer basket, working in batches if needed. Step3: Cook, turning once halfway through, until tender, about 10 minutes. Step4: Meanwhile, for gremolata, stir together parsley, garlic, and lemon zest in a small bowl. Step5: For red pepper aioli stir together mayonnaise, roasted red peppers, olive oil, red wine vinegar; and garlic in a small bowl. Step6: Top roasted vegetables with gremolata and serve with red pepper aioli.
ingredients: 1 zucchini, cut into 1/4-x3-inch pieces (about1 cup), 1 summer squash, sliced, 1/4 inch thick (about 1 cup), 1 (8-ounces) pkg. cremini mushrooms, halved orquartered if large, 3/4 cup cauliflower florets, 6 desired-color mini bell peppers, 2 teaspoon vegetable oil, 1/4 teaspoon salt, 1/4 teaspoon freshly ground black pepper, 1/2 cup chopped fresh parsley, 2 teaspoon minced fresh garlic, 2 teaspoon lemon zest, Red Pepper Aioli, 1/2 cup mayonnaise, 2 tablespoons chopped jarred roasted redpeppers, drained, 1 tablespoon extra-virgin olive oil, 1 tablespoon red wine vinegar, 1 teaspoon minced fresh garlic

title: Easy Air Fryer Baked Potatoes
description: Try air fryer baked potatoes and don't look back. Use this handy appliance to make tender, delicious baked potatoes with a crispy, flavorful skin.
directions: Step1: Preheat an air fryer to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C). Step2: Rub potatoes with olive oil and season with salt, pepper, garlic powder, and parsley. Place potatoes in the air fryer basket. Step3: Cook in the preheated air fryer until potatoes are soft, 40 to 50 minutes, depending on potato size. Step4: Slice potatoes lengthwise. Pinch both sides of each potato, using your hands and forcing potatoes to open, until the fluffy insides start to come out. Add 1 tablespoon of butter into each potato.
ingredients: 4 large baking potatoes, scrubbed, 2 tablespoons olive oil, kosher salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste, 0.5 teaspoon garlic powder, or to taste, 0.5 teaspoon dried parsley, or to taste, 4 tablespoons butter

title: Air Fryer Ranch Chicken Bites
description: Ranch flavored chicken bites are quickly cooked in the air fryer and topped with melted Cheddar cheese.
directions: Step1: Combine chicken, avocado oil, white vinegar, ranch powder, garlic powder, salt, and pepper in a large bowl. Stir well until the chicken is coated, cover, and marinate in the fridge for 30 to 60 minutes, but not much longer, as the texture will become mushy. Step2: Preheat the air fryer to 380 degrees F (190 degrees C). Place chicken cubes in the air fryer basket in a single layer, not touching. Step3: Air fry until chicken is no longer pink in the center and the juices run clear, flipping once when the edges start to brown, being sure not to overcook, 8 to 11 minutes. An instant-read thermometer inserted near the bone should read 165 degrees F (74 degrees C). Your cooking time may vary depending on the brand and size of your air fryer, and you may need to cook in batches. Step4: Sprinkle the chicken with Cheddar cheese. Return to the air fryer until cheese melts, for about 30 seconds. Serve warm, garnished with chopped parsley.
ingredients: 1 pound boneless, skinless chicken thighs, trimmed and cut into 1-inch cubes, 2 tablespoons avocado oil, 1 tablespoon white vinegar, 1.5 teaspoons dry ranch dressing mix (such as Hidden Valley Ranch®), 1 teaspoon garlic powder, 0.5 teaspoon salt, 0.5 teaspoon freshly ground black pepper, 3 tablespoons shredded extra-sharp Cheddar cheese, 1 tablespoon chopped fresh parsley

title: Air Fryer BBQ Chicken Drummies
description: These chicken drummies cooked in the air fryer are perfectly crisp on the outside, tender and juicy on the inside.
directions: Step1: Preheat an air fryer to 360 degrees F (180 degrees C). Step2: Place drummies in a large bowl. Add olive oil, garlic powder, salt, and pepper. Mix until evenly combined. Spread out drummies in the basket of the air fryer. Step3: Cook drummies for 25 minutes. Step4: Using tongs, remove drummies from the air fryer and place in a large bowl. Pour barbecue over the top and shake to coat. Step5: Place coated drummies back in the basket of the air fryer. Cook until drummies are no longer pink at the bone and the juices run clear, about 5 more minutes. An instant-read thermometer inserted near the bone should read 165 degrees F (74 degrees C). Serve immediately.
ingredients: 2 pounds chicken drummies, 1.5 tablespoons olive oil, 1 teaspoon garlic powder, 0.5 teaspoon salt, 0.13 teaspoon freshly ground black pepper, 0.75 cup barbecue sauce

title: Air Fryer Chicken Bites with Parmesan Cheese
description: Chicken pieces are cooked until crisp in the air fryer and topped with melted Parmesan cheese. Serve with marinara sauce for dipping.
directions: Step1: Whisk olive oil, Worcestershire, Italian seasoning, garlic powder, salt, and pepper together in a bowl. Add chicken cubes and stir to coat. Step2: Preheat an air fryer to 370 degrees F (185 degrees C) for 10 minutes. Step3: Add flour to the chicken mixture and stir to coat until all liquid is absorbed. Step4: Place chicken in the basket of the air fryer and cook for 8 minutes. Using tongs, flip the pieces over. Spray tops with non-stick cooking spray and cook 8 minutes more. Step5: Sprinkle Parmesan cheese and parsley over the chicken. Cook until cheese has started to melt, about 2 minutes more. Serve immediately.
ingredients: 2 teaspoons olive oil, 2 teaspoons Worcestershire sauce, 1 teaspoon dried Italian seasoning, 0.5 teaspoon garlic powder, 0.25 teaspoon salt, 0.13 teaspoon freshly ground black pepper, 1 pound skinless, boneless chicken breast, cut into 1-inch cubes, 2 tablespoons all-purpose flour, cooking spray, 0.25 cup shredded Parmesan cheese, 2 tablespoons chopped fresh parsley

title: Air Fryer Crispy Cajun Black-Eyed Peas
description: Crispy outside, creamy inside, air fryer-puffed and Cajun-spiced, these black-eyed peas will be your new favorite healthy snack.
directions: Step1: Line a baking sheet with paper towels; spread drained peas out in an even layer, discarding shells and mushed peas. Pat dry with additional paper towels. Step2: Preheat an air fryer to 400 degrees Fahrenheit (200 degrees C) according to manufacturer's instructions. Step3: Whisk oil and Cajun seasoning in a bowl. Stir in peas until evenly coated. Step4: Place peas in the basket of the air fryer. Cook for 7 minutes. Shake the basket and cook 7 minutes more.
ingredients: 1 (14.5 ounce) can black-eyed peas, rinsed and drained, 1 tablespoon olive oil, 1.5 teaspoons Cajun seasoning (such as Old Bay®)

title: Air Fryer Roasted Garlic
description: Roast garlic in the air fryer for a quick and easy way to add flavor to lots of dishes. Add to pasta sauces, mashed potatoes, or use for garlic toast.
directions: Step1: Preheat the air fryer to 380 degrees F (190 degrees C). Step2: Cut the top off the head of garlic and place on a square piece of aluminum foil. Bring the foil up and around garlic. Pour olive oil on top and season with salt and pepper. Close ends of foil over garlic, creating a pouch. Step3: Air fry until garlic is soft, 16 to 20 minutes. Open the foil pouch very carefully, as hot steam will escape.
ingredients: 1 head garlic, aluminum foil, 1 teaspoon extra-virgin olive oil, 0.25 teaspoon salt, 0.25 teaspoon ground black pepper

title: Air Fryer Puffed Butter Beans
description: Crispy on the outside, creamy on the inside, these puffed butter beans cooked in the air fryer will be your new favorite healthy snack.
directions: Step1: Stir together butter beans, olive oil, salt, pepper, and garlic powder in a bowl until combined. Spread out in the air fryer basket Step2: Preheat an air fryer to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C). Step3: Air fry until golden and crispy, tossing halfway through, for 12 to 15 minutes. Step4: Sprinkle with additional seasonings to taste if you like. Store in an air-tight container for 3 to 5 days.
ingredients: 1 (16 ounce) can large butter beans, drained and rinsed, 1 tablespoon olive oil, 1 teaspoon salt, 1 teaspoon freshly ground black pepper, 1 teaspoon garlic powder, Optional: preferred seasoning blend

title: Air Fryer Spicy Onion Rings
description: These onion rings get a nice spicy flavor from adobo and chili and lime seasonings. Cooking them in the air fryer is much healthier than deep frying.
directions: Step1: Whisk together buttermilk, egg, flour, chile and lime seasoning, and adobo seasoning for the batter in a shallow bowl. Cover and refrigerate for 30 minutes. Step2: Combine panko, adobo seasoning, and chile and lime seasoning in a shallow dish; mix well. Remove batter from the fridge. Dip onion rings first into the batter, then into bread crumb mixture, turning to coat, and gently shake off excess crumbs. Lightly spritz the onion rings with cooking spray on both sides. Step3: Preheat the air fryer to 340 degrees F (170 degrees C). Line the air fryer basket with a parchment liner or lightly spray with oil. Step4: Place the breaded onion rings into the fryer basket in an even layer, leaving about 1/2-inch space between the slices. Step5: Cook until crisp and lightly browned, flipping halfway through, 10 to 12 minutes. You may have to cook in batches, and cooking time may vary depending on the size and brand of your air fryer. Step6: Remove from the air fryer, transfer to a baking sheet, sprinkle with kosher salt, and place in a 250 degrees F (120 degrees C) oven to keep warm.
ingredients: 2 large sweet onions, sliced 1/2 inch thick, 0.67 cup buttermilk, 1 egg, 0.25 cup all-purpose flour, 1 teaspoon RedHot Chile and Lime Seasoning Blend (such as Frank's®), 0.5 teaspoon adobo all-purpose seasoning (such as Goya®), 2 cups panko bread crumbs, 1 teaspoon adobo all-purpose seasoning (such as Goya®), 0.5 teaspoon RedHot Chile and Lime Seasoning Blend (such as Frank's®), olive oil cooking spray, 1 teaspoon kosher salt, or to taste

title: Air Fryer Green Beans
description: The fresh flavors of summer come alive in these air fryer green beans, a very simple side dish. They pair well with grilled chicken, fish or pork.
directions: Step1: Preheat the air fryer to 380 degrees F (195 degrees C). Step2: Place green beans, olive oil, lemon juice, salt, and pepper in a large bowl and toss to coat. Using tongs, place green beans into the air fryer basket without overcrowding, reserving any remaining liquid in the bowl. You may need to work in batches, depending on the size of your air fryer. Step3: Cook green beans until crisp-tender, 8 to 10 minutes, shaking the basket halfway through. When green beans are done, return to the bowl and toss with the lemon zest. Serve with additional lemon wedges.
ingredients: 1 pound fresh green beans, ends trimmed, 1 1/2 tablespoons olive oil, 2 teaspoons lemon juice, 1/2 teaspoon lemon zest, salt and pepper, to taste, 4 lemon wedges

title: Air Fryer Chicken Tenders
description: Air fryer cooked chicken tenders are quick and easy to make and will surely become a family favorite.
directions: Step1: Preheat air fryer to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Coat basket with cooking spray. Step2: Whisk egg in a small bowl. In another bowl, stir together panko and oil until loose and crumbly. Step3: Dip each chicken tender into egg, allowing excess to drip off. Dip chicken in panko mixture to coat completely. Working in batches if needed, arrange chicken in an even layer in the air fryer basket. Step4: Cook until chicken is no longer pink in the center and the juices run clear, about 12 minutes. An instant-read thermometer inserted into the center should read at least 165 degrees F (74 degrees C). Garnish with parsley and serve with honey-mustard sauce.
ingredients: 1 egg, ½ cup panko bread crumbs, 2 tablespoons canola oil, 8 chicken tenders (about 1 lb.), Chopped fresh parsley, for garnish, Honey-mustard sauce, for serving

title: Air Fryer Frozen Chicken Strips
description: Use an air fryer to quickly and easily cook frozen chicken strips to golden, crispy perfection in minutes.
directions: Step1: Set the air fryer temperature to 380 degrees F (180 degrees C). Step2: Place frozen chicken strips in the air fryer basket, without touching or overcrowding. Step3: Cook until crispy, 11 to 12 minutes. The color will not change much. You may have to cook in batches depending on the size of your air fryer, and cooking time may vary depending on the brand and size of your air fryer. Step4: Remove from the air fryer and serve immediately.
ingredients: 25 ounces frozen cooked, breaded crispy chicken strips (such as Tyson®)

title: Air Fryer Blooming Onion
description: Use your air fryer to prepare this blooming onion, a fun appetizer resembling a flower. Serve with dipping sauce as a shared appetizer.
directions: Step1: Preheat air fryer to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C). Step2: Whisk together milk and egg in a bowl until combined. In a large bowl, stir together flour, salt, cayenne pepper, paprika, black pepper, oregano, thyme, and cumin. Step3: Slice 1 inch off the top of the onion and remove papery skin. Remove a 1-inch-diameter core from the middle of the onion, using an apple corer or paring knife, leaving the very bottom of the root end intact. Use a large sharp knife to slice about three-fourths of the way down center of the onion; turn onion 90 degrees and slice again. Keep slicing each section in half until you have 16 sections, being careful not to cut through the bottom of the onion. Spread sections apart. Step4: Dip onion into milk mixture and then into flour mixture to coat, separating the petals and sprinkling flour mixture between them. Dip onion into milk mixture again, then into flour mixture to coat once more. Coat onion with cooking spray. Step5: Arrange onion in the air fryer basket. Cook until crispy, 20 to 25 minutes. Step6: Stir together mayonnaise, horseradish sauce, ketchup, paprika, salt, dried oregano, cayenne pepper, and black pepper in a small bowl. Chill until blooming onion is ready. Step7: Serve blooming onion with dipping sauce and garnish with additional paprika.
ingredients: Blooming Onion, 1 cup milk, 1 egg, 1 cup flour, 3/4 teaspoon salt, 3/4 teaspoon cayenne pepper, 1/2 teaspoon paprika, plus more for garnish, 1/4 teaspoon freshly ground black pepper, 1/4 teaspoon dried oregano, 1/8 teaspoon dried thyme, 1/8 teaspoon cumin, 1 (14- to 16-ounces) sweet onion, Dipping Sauce, 1/2 cup mayonnaise, 2 tablespoons cream-style horseradish sauce, 1 tablespoon ketchup, 1/4 teaspoon each paprika and salt, 1/8 teaspoon dried oregano, 1/8 teaspoon cayenne pepper, 1 pinch black pepper

title: Air Fryer Samosas
description: Use your air fryer to make Indian samosas - this version is vegetarian with potatoes and peas but you can cook any samosa in the air fryer.
directions: Step1: Add potatoes to a small saucepan and cover with salted water; bring to a boil over high heat. Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes or until fork-tender. Drain and transfer potatoes to a bowl; mash until mostly smooth with a few small chunks remaining. Step2: In the same saucepan, heat oil over medium heat. Add onion and cook, stirring occasionally, until tender, 3 to 4 minutes. Stir in ginger and garlic; cook until fragrant, about 30 seconds. Add garam masala, cumin, salt, and (if using) cayenne; cook about 30 seconds more. Stir in mashed potatoes and peas; cook until warmed through. Remove from heat; stir in cilantro. Step3: Arrange wonton wrappers on a clean work surface; evenly spoon filling into centers of wontonwrappers. Lightly wet borders of wrappers with water. Fold two corners together to form triangles. Press edges to seal. Coat both sides of samosas with cooking spray. Step4: Preheat air fryer to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Coat air fryer basket with cooking spray. Step5: Working in batches if needed, arrange samosas in an even layer in the basket. Cook, turning once halfway through, until samosas are golden brown and crispy, about 8 minutes. Step6: Meanwhile, combine yogurt, cilantro, lime zest, lime juice; garlic, salt and pepper in a small food processor; process until well combined. Chill, covered, up to 5 days.  Step7: Serve samosas with cilantro-yogurt sauce. Garnish with additional cilantro.
ingredients: 12 ounces Yukon gold potatoes, peeled and cutinto 1-inch pieces, 1 tablespoon extra-virgin olive oil, 1/2 cup chopped onion, 1 teaspoon grated fresh ginger, 2 cloves garlic, minced, 1 teaspoon garam masala, 1/2 teaspoon cumin, 1/4 teaspoon salt, 1/8 teaspoon cayenne pepper (optional), 2/3 cup frozen peas, thawed, 1/4 cup chopped fresh cilantro, plus more forgarnish, 24 wonton wrappers, Cilantro-Yogurt Sauce, 3/4 cup whole-milk Greek-style yogurt, 1/3 cup chopped fresh cilantro, 1 teaspoon lime zest, 1 tablespoon lime juice, 1 clove garlic, chopped,  1 pincheach salt, 1 pinch black pepper

title: Simple Air Fryer Brussels Sprouts
description: Air fryer Brussels sprouts come out crispy on the outsides, tender on the insides, and delicious all the way through! Plus you'll use only a little oil.
directions: Step1: Preheat an air fryer to 390 degrees F (200 degrees C) for 15 minutes. Step2: While the air fryer is preheating, trim Brussels sprouts. Place in a bowl with olive oil, garlic powder, salt, and pepper in a bowl and mix well. Spread sprouts evenly in the air fryer basket. Step3: Cook in the preheated air fryer for 15 minutes, shaking the basket halfway through the cycle.
ingredients: 1.5 pounds Brussels sprouts, 2 tablespoons olive oil, 1 teaspoon garlic powder, 1 teaspoon salt, 0.5 teaspoon ground black pepper
prep: Preheat an air fryer to 390 degrees F (200 degrees C) for 15 minutes.

title: Air Fryer Honey Garlic Chicken Wings
description: These crispy air fryer honey garlic chicken wings are a flavor explosion in your mouth–the perfect combination of crispy, juicy chicken wings and a sticky-sweet honey garlic sauce, with just the right amount of heat from cayenne pepper.
directions: Step1: Preheat the air fryer to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C). Step2: Mix baking powder, salt, black pepper, garlic powder, paprika, and cayenne pepper together in a small bowl. Step3: Pat chicken wings dry with paper towels, then toss them in spice mixture until evenly coated. Arrange wings in a single layer in the air fryer basket. Step4: Cook wings in the preheated air fryer until crispy and golden brown, juices are clear, and meat is no longer pink at the bone, 20 to 25 minutes. An instant-read thermometer inserted near the bone should read 165 degrees F (74 degrees C). Step5: Meanwhile, make the honey garlic sauce. Stir honey, soy sauce, garlic, and ginger together in a small saucepan over medium heat. Step6: In a separate small bowl, whisk together cornstarch and water until smooth, then add to the saucepan. Cook until sauce thickens, 1 to 2 minutes. Step7: Transfer wings to a large bowl, pour honey garlic sauce over wings, and toss to coat evenly. Garnish with chopped green onions and serve hot.
ingredients: 1 tablespoon baking powder, 1 teaspoon salt, 1/2 teaspoon black pepper, 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder, 1/2 teaspoon paprika, 1/4 teaspoon cayenne pepper, 2 pounds chicken wings, 1/2 cup honey, 1/4 cup soy sauce, 2 cloves garlic, minced, 1 tablespoon grated ginger, 1 tablespoon cornstarch, 1 tablespoon water, 2 tablespoons chopped green onions

title: Air Fryer Smoked Salmon Wontons
description: You only need 5 ingredients for these delicious wonton appetizers filled with cream cheese and smoked salmon.
directions: Step1: Combine cream cheese, salmon, capers, and red onion in a bowl. Fill a second small bowl with water. Step2: Working with 6 wonton wrappers at a time, separate them out onto a clean work surface. Place 1 teaspoon of salmon mixture in the center of each wonton. Do not overfill, as the mixture may ooze out. Step3: Dip your finger in the bowl of water, and lightly wet the 4 edges of each wonton wrapper. Gently fold in half diagonally to make a triangle, and seal the edges. Try not to leave excess air in the wonton, which can cause them to burst. Lightly wet the bottom of the triangle, and fold the right side over the middle, then the left side, pressing all edges to seal. Set wontons aside, covered with a damp paper towel, while you finish making the remaining wontons. Step4: Preheat the air fryer to 330 degrees F (166 degrees C). Generously mist both sides of wontons with cooking spray. Step5: Place as many wontons in the air fryer basket as will fit, without overcrowding. Step6: Air-fry for 5 minutes, flipping halfway through. Remove to a cooling rack and let cool while you cook the remaining wontons in batches. Best served slightly warm or at room temperature.
ingredients: 1 (6 ounce) package cream cheese, softened, 3 ounces cold-smoked salmon, finely chopped, 1.5 tablespoons minced capers, 1.5 tablespoons finely minced red onion, 48 wonton wrappers, water as needed, cooking spray
